snippet.title: Mbosso - Pawa (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
Music video by Mbosso performing, “Pawa” (Power), is a heartfelt, poetic love song by Mbosso that captures the overwhelming power of deep affection. Using rich metaphors and smooth vocals, he likens love to an intoxicating force that leaves him weak and emotionally charged — “naishiwa pawa” (I’m losing power). The lyrics blend vulnerability with admiration, painting his lover as a source of strength and inspiration. With a melodic blend of Bongo Flava and soulful instrumentation, “Pawa” showcases Mbosso’s lyrical depth and emotive style. The music was shot in Iringa, Tanzania, Directed by Folex & Audio produced by S2Kizzy.

snippet.title: Kenya descends into CHAOS as MASSIVE violent protests erupt against police brutality
snippet.description:
Thousands of protesters took to the streets in Nairobi on Wednesday, clashing with police over issues of police brutality and government corruption, as demonstrations spread nationwide.

The confrontations saw police deploying tear gas and using batons, resulting in several injuries. These protests coincide with the one-year anniversary of anti-tax demonstrations that led to 60 deaths and left 20 individuals missing.

The unrest has now extended to major cities such as Mombasa, Kisumu, Nakuru, and Nyahururu, evolving into demands for the president's resignation over allegations of poor governance.

Kenyan youth are particularly dissatisfied with the current administration, citing corruption, a rising cost of living, and police brutality, further fuelled by the recent death of a blogger in custody.

Public anger has been intensified by the close-range shooting of a civilian during recent demonstrations.

snippet.title: Two people shot dead in protests marking one year since anti-govt demos in Kenya
snippet.description:
Two people have died after being shot while protesting in Kenya.
Demonstrators are marking a year since at least 60 people were killed in antigovernment demonstrations.
In the capital, Nairobi, Parliament and the President's office have been barricaded.
Last June protests against government tax reforms turned deadly.
Demonstrators stormed parliament and President William Ruto dissolved the cabinet to try to appease the protesters. 
They accused the government of corruption and mismanagement.

Al Jazeera’s Catherine Soi has more on the protests and Malcolm Webb has the latest updates from Nairobi.

snippet.title: Diamond Platnumz feat Bien - Katam (Official Lyric Audio)
snippet.description:
Get Katam👇👇👇
https://dplatnumz.lnk.to/katam

"KATAM" is a sweet, catchy love anthem that brings together two East African powerhouses—Diamond Platnumz and @BienOfficial in a celebration of beauty, love, and unity across the continent. snippet.title: Kenya Protest LIVE: Massive Protests Turn Violent in Kenya; Police, Protesters Clash in Nairobi
snippet.description:
Kenya Protest LIVE: Massive Protests Turn Violent in Kenya; Police, Protesters Clash in Nairobi | Kenya Blogger Death | N18G

Kenyans demonstrate against police brutality following the death of blogger Albert Ojwang in police custody under unclear circumstances earlier in June and the shooting of hawker Boniface Kariuki at close range by police during protests on June 18. The protests coincide with the one-year anniversary of the storming of the Kenyan parliament by anti-tax demonstrators, during which several activists and protesters were abducted and killed by police. Kenya has a history of police brutality and President William Ruto has previously vowed to end it.

snippet.title: Nairobi LIVE: Thousands Rally in Kenya To Mark Anniversary of Antitax Demonstrations | GenZ | N18G
snippet.description:
Kenya Protest LIVE: Tension Escalates as Protesters March to Central Police Station | Ojwang | CNBC TV18
Nairobi, Kenya - Demonstrators in Nairobi mark the anniversary of deadly 2024 anti-government protests.
Gen Z Anniversary: Tension Escalates as Protesters March to Central Police Station, Teargas Fired 
Kenyans demonstrate against police brutality following the death of blogger Albert Ojwang in police custody under unclear circumstances earlier in June and the shooting of hawker Boniface Kariuki at close range by police during protests on June 18. The protests coincide with the one-year anniversary of the storming of the Kenyan parliament by anti-tax demonstrators, during which several activists and protesters were abducted and killed by police. Kenya has a history of police brutality and President William Ruto has previously vowed to end it.
Ojwang had been arrested at his home in Homa Bay and transported to Nairobi, where he was locked up at the station. Following his death, disturbing reports surfaced alleging that he had been physically abused while in custody. It was claimed that he was severely beaten in the cells before being rushed to Mbagathi Hospital, where he was declared dead. 

#KENYA #nairobi #kenyaprotests #kenyapolitics #southafrica #livenews #cnbctv18

localized.description:
Tensions erupted on the streets of Nairobi as protesters clashed with unidentified men wielding clubs amid demonstrations over the controversial death of a popular blogger. What began as a peaceful protest quickly descended into chaos, with visuals showing groups of attackers targeting demonstrators in broad daylight. The incident has sparked outrage across Kenya, raising serious questions about the safety of free expression and the role of law enforcement. Stay tuned for the latest updates from ground zero.

snippet.title: Kenyan protestors set-up road-blocks against police in Nairobi | AFP
snippet.description:
Protestors set up makeshift barricades on the streets of Nairobi, as Kenya marks the one year anniversary of the deadly storming of the parliament. This as police in riot gear try and disperse crowds with tear gas.
